This paper deals with computer vision tasks related to motion prediction and modeling of mirror neurons, which are closely related to the fields of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep neural networks for training models also suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for building autonomous intelligent systems, which could also fall under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE).
